      "text": "Over the last decade I was a pretty busy framework user. I used all kinds of technical frameworks for GUIs (e.g. MVC & [[Application Model]]s), graphical editors (e.g. [[Object Drawing]]) and persistence (e.g. EXDI, [[Store Talk]], [[Top Link]]). Over the last 2 years I also used a domain framework for derivatives trading, called [[Universal Finance Server]]. Parallel to using frameworks I was also developing and/or extending them, especially in the area of persistence (mapping objects to relational databases), GUIs (building on top of [[Visual Works]] [[Application Model]]s) and derivatives trading (extending the [[Universal Finance Server]]).",
      "id": "232bcc910810ab6c9b675b7456e6b98d"
