      "text": "\nFirst of all, an object-oriented framework cannot be developed in one go, it has to be developed <i>iteratively</i>. Instead of passively monitoring the typical evolution of your framework (white-box to black-box to toolkit) you should plan, implement and deliver at least three versions of your framework. Because this is the only way to get a framework that satisfies the actual needs of your users without carrying too much unneeded flexibility with it. See [[Evolving Frameworks]] for more details on this. ",
      "id": "e4f3af614f9776d5f4d6556d010a1ccd"
