      "type": "html",
      "text": "\nThe most important thing is simplicity when it comes to the nature of your framework. And the most reliable way to destroy simplicity is adding unneeded flexibility. That's why iterative development is so important. Additionally we should use standards and well known design patterns wherever possible to reuse the know-how that people already have. Last, but not least, we should build our frameworks on a small set of central abstractions and use those consistently. A very nice example is the [[Tools And Materials Metaphor]].",
      "id": "51e3944dbf1939c8b9a940e22cacd8b1"
